Title: AI adoption will lead to more specialised jobs and need for newer skill sets - IndiaTimes

name: AI adoption will lead to more specialised jobs and need for newer skill sets
headline: AI adoption will lead to more specialised jobs and need for newer skill sets
articleBody: Disruptions caused by the pandemic have fast-tracked the adoption of Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning across industry sectors, which in turn will have a lasting impact on employment over the next several years.Experts said while the verdict is not yet out on the number of jobs created or displaced as a result of rapid adoption of AI and automation, it will lead to more specialised jobs and need for newer skill sets.“Across industries, the nature of work is transforming, and the change is happening at two levels - new types of jobs are being created, and roles are being reconfigured,” said Aditya Priyadarshan, Managing Director, Strategy & Consulting - Talent & Organisation, Accenture in India. “As AI and other intelligent technologies take the form of ‘co-workers’ by undertaking routine work, people have the opportunity to put their energies into more strategic and creative tasks.”AI and chatbots now assist in resume screening and hiring, predicting the right candidate and making recruitment more efficient; robots are being increasinglyused on manufacturing shop-floors, and intelligent technologies will replace roles that are repetitive in structure.Covid disruptions enhanced the adoption of AI.“The pace of disruption due to the deployment of automation and AI is dramatically accelerated by virtual mode of work and massive increase in e-commerce and digital,” said Faridun Dotiwala, Partner, McKinsey & Company. “Globally, there would be a planned reduction in office space by 30% and 1 to 5x growth in e-commerce.”In a global McKinsey survey of 800 executives, two-thirds claimed they were significantly stepping up investments in AI and automation. It also highlighted the high correlation between the use of AI and work arenas with high levels of human interaction. Almost 100 million workers may need to switch occupations by 2030 in eight countries (the US, the UK, Germany, Japan, France, Spain, China and India).Future of Tech@Work“AI or any experiential technology has historically created more jobs than they destroyed,” said Anurag Malik, Partner, People Advisory Services, EY India. “Repetitive roles will get replaced by RPA (Robotic Process Automation) and AI 4-5 years down the line, while the quality of roles and work will improve.”Mahindra & Mahindra has been focusing on industrial automation to build more capacity much before the pandemic. It is looking at intelligent technologies to improve customer experience and enhance employee productivity.“This phase will be focused on using AI to make cars more intelligent and making employees more productive,” said Mohit Kapoor, chief technology officer, Mahindra Group. Others such as leading conglomerate RPG Group, which has been using AI across its various businesses, has fast-tracked adoption.“Remote working has prompted us to use technology in the hiring process. From using intelligent screening software that adds a lot of punch to background verification to using recruiter chatbots to do digital interviews - we have rolled out AI in hiring across all our businesses,” said Somraj Roy, CHRO, KEC International, a part of the RPG Group.FMCG major Marico is considering the use of chatbots to engage with prospective candidates and of AI enabled CV analysis, said CHRO Amit Prakash.“Organisations can use data to figure out patterns and see if there's any skew while making decisions, and then use that to make better hiring decisions,” said Chaitanya N Sreenivas - Vice President & HR Head, IBM, India and South Asia.Accelerated adoption of AI will also lead to the creation of newer kinds of jobs. Key emerging jobs we can expect right now are in AI, ML, IoT, data, security and information security, privacy, cloud computing, signal processing – data analysts, data scientists, big data specialists, and people who can develop software at various levels,” said Anjali Rao, Senior Director - HR, Intel India.Skilling will play a crucial role, and India could lose nearly $2 trillion by 2028 without up-skilling, with higher unemployment, shows an Accenture study.“The human-machine partnership will require a different mindset and skills to thrive in the future where social, cognitive, and technological skills will be in high demand,  said Akhilesh Nair, Global Hiring Leader, Genpact.

headline: Top Artificial Intelligence Research Jobs Across the World
articleBody: Job alert! Top companies are hiring for Artificial Intelligence Research Jobs across the world..Artificial Intelligence refers to the reconstruction of human understanding in robots that are programmed to think and act like people. AI has transformed a once-obscure technology into a common toolkit for software engineering and design. AI is, without a doubt, the future of automation. Artificial Intelligence careers are at the heart of emerging IT innovations such as robotization, DevOps phases, the Internet Chabot, and mechanical technology. Artificial Intelligence Research Jobs is a fast-paced, high-risk area that is making significant inroads into our everyday lives. Here, we will mention some top Artificial Intelligence Research Jobs across the globe..1. Manager of Artificial Intelligence (Computer Vision) at Infilect.Location: Bengaluru, Karnataka, India.About the Company: Infilect was created by two PhDs and ex-IBM-Research-Scientists to create scalable visual-AI systems that would improve the world..Roles and Responsibility:.Managing a team of 4 to 6 AI developers to create a Computer Vision platform for the retail industry (Deep Learning, DataOps, MLOps)Working with the data labeling team, product engineering manager, product managers, and the CTO to develop, engineer, and contribute to the deployment of a modular Deep Learning-based image recognition platform..Qualification: 6 to 10 years of Machine Learning experience, 2 to 4 years of experience in deep learning.Click here to apply.2. Artificial Intelligence Data Analyst at Rapid Innovation.Location: India.About the company: Rapid Innovation is a blockchain app development firm that specializes in assisting entrepreneurs and start-ups in creating innovative solutions that serve to decentralize the internet..Roles and Responsibility:.Advise C-suite and corporate leaders on a wide variety of AI-related technical, strategy, and policy challenges.Working with an advanced engineering team and senior leadership, work on functional design, process design prototype, testing, training, and developing support processes..Qualification:.A bachelor's degree in computer science is required.2+ years of AI application expertise in a realistic and thorough technology.Click here to apply.3. Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning Expert at smartSense Consulting Solutions.Location: Gujrat, Gandhinagar, India.About the Company: smartSense Consulting Solutions is a prominent IT firm that serves clients in a variety of industries..Roles and Responsibility:.Design and design an architecture for Machine Learning models that will be deployed in dockerized containers using CI and CD.Create models for a variety of text categorization and entity recognition scenarios..Qualification: Minimum of 3 years of Machine Learning, dataset preparation, and model development expertise.Click here to apply.4. Senior Artificial Intelligence Engineer at DIMAAG-AI.Location: Bengaluru, Karnataka, India.About the Company: DIMAAG-AI is committed to smoothly integrating our cutting-edge AI technologies into your organization..Roles and Responsibility:.Ability to operate as part of a team to achieve a common objective.Execution that is self-managed and results-oriented..Qualification: Master's or Bachelor's degree in engineering is required..Click here to apply.5. Artificial Intelligence Researcher at Cactus Communications.Location: India.About the Company: Cactus Communications is a technological firm that helps scientists progress faster..Roles and Responsibilities:.Immerse yourself in developing cutting-edge solutions to large-scale issues in the actual world.You have to work alongside engineers and researchers on something significant and worthwhile..Qualification: A master's or doctoral degree in computer science is required..Click here to apply.6. AWS Analyst Relations Manager, Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) at Amazon Web Services (AWS).Location: Austin, TX.About the Company: Amazon Web Services (AWS) began exposing critical infrastructure services to businesses in the form of web services in 2006, which is now often referred to as cloud computing..Roles and Responsibilities:.Develop and implement a worldwide AR campaign to educate the analyst community about Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning.Proactively manage vendor assessments, and ensure that AWS is mentioned positively in critical reports..Qualification: A bachelor's degree or equivalent work experience is required..Click here to apply.7. Artificial Intelligence Senior Consultant, Advisory at Avanade .Location: Chicago, IL.About the Company: On the Microsoft ecosystem, Avanade is the premier provider of innovative digital and cloud services, business solutions, and design-led experiences..Roles and Responsibilities: You will have to work with senior client executives (C-levels, VPs, Directors) to define our customers' data and analytics or Artificial Intelligence strategy, transformation initiatives, investments, and operating models to support their business goals..Qualification: A bachelor's degree in a relevant subject is required, with an MBA desirable..Click here to apply.8. Artificial Intelligence, Scientist at Charles River Analytics .Location: Cambridge, MA.About the Company: Charles River Analytics performs cutting-edge AI, robotics, and human-machine interaction research and development, and then uses that research to create unique solutions for your company..Roles and Responsibilities:.Using AI techniques that are both symbolic and sub-symbolicTo describe novel AI systems, programming languages and domain-specific languages are being developed.Developing clever interactive virtual agents.Qualification: Ph.D. in Computer Science or comparable professional experience in Artificial Intelligence or Adaptive Training is required..Click here to apply.9. Visiting Researcher, Artificial Intelligence (Ph.D.) at Facebook.Location: New York.About the Company: Facebook's purpose, from its inception in 2004, has been to empower individuals to create communities and bring the globe closer together..Roles and Responsibilities:.Conduct research in the field of intelligent systems science and technology.Collaborate on existing research projects to boost productivity.Conduct research to enhance computational understanding and data representation..Qualification: A Ph.D. in a technological subject (e.g., Computer Science).Click here to apply.10. Artificial Intelligence Senior Consultant, Advisory at Avanade.Location: Boston, MA.About the Company: On the Microsoft ecosystem, Avanade is the premier provider of innovative digital and cloud services, business solutions, and design-led experiences..Roles and Responsibilities: Support the delivery of a wide range of data, analytics, advanced analytics, visualization, Data Science, robotic process automation, and Artificial Intelligence (AI) strategy and advisory engagements..Qualifications: A bachelor's degree in a relevant subject is required, with an MBA desirable..Click here to apply.Disclaimer: Analytics Insight does not provide financial advice or guidance. Title: AI, ML or Data Science? Which is the Best Path to Take? - Analytics Insight
title: N/A

name: AI, ML or Data Science? Which is the Best Path to Take?
headline: AI, ML or Data Science? Which is the Best Path to Take?
articleBody: AI, ML, or Data Science, which is best for you?.Artificial intelligence, machine learning, and data science are the most trending topics in the present era. All these terms fall under the same domain but they have their individual applications and meaning. For the tech companies, the application of these terms is given the top list priority. Even the job hirings for these domains is increasing at a high rate. It has increased 74% according to Linkedin's 2019 "Emerging Jobs" report. The salary offered to a data scientist and AI engineer is quite high which is above US$100k. The growing need for talents in such jobs has triggered a number of universities to provide degrees in those domains, many new courses, diplomas, full-time courses, private boot camps have emerged and also are still emerging. But a question arises about which domain's course should be taken up. Is it AI, ML, or data science? Is there any difference?.Answering this, yes there are differences but the difference is not a definite one. There is a very thin line of boundaries among the three which cannot be ignored. Many universities tend to ignore the boundary and provide degree programs based on the combination of the three. This makes students unclear about which field their focus is on. So, it is important to mark the differences and provide proper guidance to the students..Where does the difference lie between the three domains?.Artificial intelligence refers to machines that have the potential to replicate the cognitive capabilities that are associated with the human mind. It is about replicating human minds' capabilities..Machine learning is generally considered to be the potentiality of a computer program to learn or boost performance through examples rather than detailed programmed rules. Machine learning is one of the essential tools which data scientists use to examine and interpret data..Data science refers to the accumulation of methods, tools, and practices of analyzing data to interpret and derive insights in order to support decision-making..Both AI and data science use machine learning as key tools. In AI, ML tools are used in real-time to allow machines to execute their action. ML is the essential tool in the field of AI to develop intelligent agents. In the field of data science, ML is used as a data analysis tool to unlock patterns in data and to make predictions..What should you learn?.After understanding three different fields of expertise, you need to think about what your goals are and which one you prefer. If you want to go for research work then preferably the field of data science is the one for you. If you want to become an engineer and want to create intelligence into software products then machine learning or more preferably AI is the best path to take..Still, if you are not sure which path to choose you can start with data science because after all data is everything, data is the key to success in all the fields whether it is AI or ML. Strong expertise in processing, cleaning, analyzing, and visualizing data, along with statistical knowledge, will benefit you no matter what path you ultimately take..But it is important to note that if you are just starting your career, try to build your domain knowledge before spending your time learning about data science or ML or AI. If you have adequate domain knowledge you will maturely understand the problem you are trying to interpret and also recognize how AI or ML or data science can play a role in solving it..Disclaimer: Analytics Insight does not provide financial advice or guidance. Also note that the cryptocurrencies mentioned/listed on the website could potentially be scams, i.e. designed to induce you to invest financial resources that may be lost forever and not be recoverable once investments are made. You are responsible for conducting your own research (DYOR) before making any investments. Read more here.
